Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.39,0:01:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.45,0:01:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.28,0:01:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.87,0:02:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{??}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.01,0:02:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks, here boy, this way!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.09,0:02:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s got so much faster, hasn’t he?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.70,0:02:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, when we first found him he was so tiny \Nwe could outrun him easily.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.40,0:02:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.04,0:02:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks, Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.68,0:02:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks! {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.01,0:02:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is where you’ve been?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.00,0:02:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been searching for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.55,0:02:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.12,0:02:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.36,0:02:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Kelly. {けりー in japanese, don't think it's in the book so can't be 100% sure what is his name, but gpt says kelly is my best bet for a boy's name }
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.76,0:02:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t mean to say \Nyou owned Binks before?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.73,0:02:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. He was mine.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.86,0:02:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh goodness! Oh goodness, oh goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.86,0:03:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.98,0:03:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The owner of Binks has turned up!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.36,0:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I must tell Miss Lewis at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.37,0:03:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.11,0:03:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.11,0:03:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Kelly, what do you mean, \Nyou had him before?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.12,0:03:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re slow on the uptake, sis. {lit: your head is bad - basically just thinly veiled way to say "you're stupid"; he's talking a bit like a yokel in general}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.60,0:03:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It means this dog belongs to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.62,0:03:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That can’t be...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.21,0:03:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks belongs to Kathleen now.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.04,0:03:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems all of you here \Nare slow on the uptake. {same, stupid}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.75,0:03:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.48,0:03:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to think—that lass Kathleen \Nfound Binks, didn’t she?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.38,0:03:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.02,0:03:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I just heard you two talking.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.62,0:03:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What, exactly?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.19,0:03:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all that about how small he was \Nwhen you first picked him up and so on.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.06,0:03:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry now.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.25,0:03:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, thank you for looking \Nafter my Binks all this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.84,0:03:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll take him back now.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.57,0:03:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, Kelly.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.84,0:04:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What proof have you \Nthat you’re his owner?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.71,0:04:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Proof?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.41,0:04:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how fond he is of me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.69,0:04:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.27,0:04:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks is friendly with everyone. {Why does this sound like its recorded in a tunnel?}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He’d wag his tail \Nfor anyone who liked dogs.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.69,0:04:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then come to my place. \NI’ve a kennel ready for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.90,0:04:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a moment, Kelly. \NYou keep calling him Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.20,0:04:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name before?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.97,0:04:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.85,0:04:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.72,0:04:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was written on his collar. \NIsn't that why you called him that too?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.63,0:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He never had a collar.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.08,0:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I did put one on him, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.82,0:04:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.02,0:04:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.05,0:04:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis, there’s a boy called Kelly \Nwho says Binks belongs to him!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.59,0:04:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.86,0:04:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.81,0:04:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.30,0:04:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.17,0:05:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.23,0:05:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.34,0:05:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.20,0:05:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop there!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.01,0:05:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.32,0:05:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.41,0:05:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.70,0:05:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.15,0:05:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.15,0:05:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.12,0:05:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.96,0:06:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t you eating, everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.17,0:06:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, how can you tuck in \Nat a time like this?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.34,0:06:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.54,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The bus driver would know\N where Kelly got off.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.51,0:06:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, that doesn’t tell us \Nwhere he lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.15,0:06:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If we go round each house \Npatiently enough, we’ll find it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.99,0:06:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe so, but how long will it take?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.79,0:06:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if you do find him, \NKelly's still the owner, so it's out of your hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.46,0:06:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s something odd.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.23,0:06:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.30,0:06:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He seemed far too slick about it all. {lit: it felt like impetus/condition was too good}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.53,0:06:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.70,0:06:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.52,0:06:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you discovered anything?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.24,0:06:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We’ve found out where Kelly lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.28,0:06:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.03,0:06:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.21,0:06:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a map.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.95,0:06:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You get off at the second stop from here.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.03,0:06:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty close!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.58,0:06:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s his home like?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.59,0:07:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,His parents keep an orchard.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.89,0:07:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like Miss Lewis \Nto call on them this Sunday. {/go visit them}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.99,0:07:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I’ll go.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.50,0:07:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if only on paper, I’m Binks’ owner.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.46,0:07:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But I… it doesn’t matter any more.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.83,0:07:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.82,0:07:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? {/what doesn't matter}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.97,0:07:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you go, it won’t bring Binks back.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.86,0:07:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s necessary to meet his parents \Nand speak with them properly.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.81,0:07:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the owner’s appeared, \Nthere’s nothing else to talk about. {/can be done}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.92,0:07:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else…
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.83,0:07:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What, you’re going to Kelly’s house?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.37,0:07:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we can’t wait until Sunday.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.97,0:07:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But…
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.18,0:07:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You would give up on him straight away, \Nso it's best if you don’t come with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.15,0:08:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... That’s not fair.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.50,0:08:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, I really do think \Nthere’s something fishy about Kelly.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.39,0:08:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He may not be Binks’ true master at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.01,0:08:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely not.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.93,0:08:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.13,0:08:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wish it were so indeed, but... {lit: if it was so, I'd be happy}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.90,0:08:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we’ll bring Binks back.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.03,0:08:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait for us, won't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.91,0:08:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.52,0:08:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the map? {may be "where is" but more likely the don't have one}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.70,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Safe and sound, \NI know it by heart. {/in my head}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.06,0:08:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That house?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.20,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.34,0:08:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.47,0:09:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.57,0:09:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.01,0:09:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.46,0:09:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.68,0:09:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.26,0:09:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.69,0:09:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly, what’s wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.70,0:09:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it your chest? {lit: is your chest aching/suffocating}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.90,0:09:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hell no it doesn't... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.53,0:09:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.01,0:09:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.65,0:09:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We never told you our names. \NI’m Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.32,0:09:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m Pat. We’re twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.54,0:09:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder you're so alike, \Nthick as two short planks, the pair of you. {lit: figures why you're alike, especially in being bad in your head - was "slow on the uptake" previously}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.49,0:09:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You little shit! {shhh :smirk:}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.06,0:09:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.53,0:09:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are your father and mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.00,0:09:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.81,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have they gone?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.73,0:10:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What business is it of yours?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.32,0:10:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When will they be back?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.90,0:10:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.41,0:10:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.77,0:10:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve really come to see \Nif Binks is mine, haven’t you?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.33,0:10:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.21,0:10:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then come and look.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.92,0:10:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the kennel has Binks painted on it. {thank god the japanese animators in their infinite wisdom didn't spell it binkusu or binggs}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.92,0:10:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, though it could \Nhave been made only lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.23,0:10:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Look properly, it’s old.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.43,0:10:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.87,0:10:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But the name seems freshly painted.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.14,0:10:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we've just touched it up. \NIs that a problem?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.44,0:10:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you understand, then be off. \NGo on, clear off!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.01,0:10:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly, may we ask something?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? {lit: you still have something?}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.40,0:10:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Won’t you let Kathleen have Binks back?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.41,0:10:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No way, I said!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.96,0:11:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, he’s mine!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.91,0:11:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We understand, but to Kathleen, \Nhe’s like a brother.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.33,0:11:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you've taken Binks away, \Nshe’s been quite crushed. {lit: greatly depressed and sad}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.62,0:11:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it! I’ll never give him back, \Nno matter what you say!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.24,0:11:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not saying forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.74,0:11:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Only until Kathleen gets over it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.43,0:11:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Kelly, do it for Kathleen. {lit: think of saving kath}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.70,0:11:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell no! Binks is my friend!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.68,0:11:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly, we understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.72,0:12:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll leave for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.52,0:12:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t bother coming again.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.14,0:12:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But in exchange, \Ntake good care of Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.19,0:12:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's obvious!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.09,0:12:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter? \NDo you want some water?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.32,0:12:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But to keep a dog chained up like that—\Nyou can’t really call that looking after him with love.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.24,0:12:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know about that?! {lit: how can there be such a thing - basically just a very strong form of "That’s not true!"}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.78,0:12:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs love to run about freely.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.55,0:12:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No chains—that’s what’s best for them.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.86,0:12:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks will become faster and faster from now on.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.93,0:12:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off the chain and let him \Nrun about to his heart’s content.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.41,0:13:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.88,0:13:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m William, Kelly’s father.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.55,0:13:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Lesley.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.99,0:13:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.29,0:13:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.66,0:13:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is, I overheard \Nmy son talking with you just now.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.80,0:13:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That dog, Binks—he wasn’t actually \NKelly’s to begin with.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.15,0:13:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry for the lie. \NI must apologise on Kelly’s behalf.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.41,0:13:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s always alone, and we are so busy \Nthat we can’t often spare the time for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.31,0:13:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So sometimes he does things like this \Nto ease his loneliness.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.88,0:13:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasn’t he any friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.52,0:13:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He can’t make them.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.06,0:13:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can’t?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.72,0:13:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is, he suffers \Nfrom a serious heart condition. {how convenient}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.68,0:13:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.30,0:13:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He can’t join in with ordinary children \Nin strenuous exercise. {how convenient [2], of course when it doesn't include running off with the dog to the bus}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.47,0:13:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why, earlier...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.07,0:14:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly can’t climb hills, \Nplay in rivers, or even go to school.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.51,0:14:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet we told him to let Binks off the chain...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.38,0:14:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We promised to reward him \Nwith a dog of his own if he undergoes a surgery.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.89,0:14:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But he just...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.36,0:14:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won’t he undergo the operation?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.46,0:14:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he’s learnt it’s a very difficult one.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.39,0:14:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then he’s been too frightened \Neven to go to hospital.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.35,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This operation requires the patient \Nto possess a strong will of his own to get better.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.35,0:14:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And... And what if Kelly \Ndoesn’t receive that operation?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.22,0:14:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Within a few days, \Nwe’ll certainly return the dog.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.22,0:14:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you won't! {episodes like this or #13 make me pro-cham, now I want to advocate for killing all boys too}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.86,0:14:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.43,0:14:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I won’t give Binks back!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.30,0:14:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.47,0:15:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.69,0:15:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll leave Binks with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.75,0:15:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.65,0:15:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.12,0:15:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Be good friends, the both of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.55,0:15:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.66,0:15:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But that's...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.29,0:15:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right. {? iindesu?}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.71,0:15:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly, we're counting on you \Nto look after Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.94,0:15:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But they already said they’d return him...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.21,0:15:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it end up like this?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.35,0:15:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.35,0:15:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe it's for the best, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.95,0:15:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! It could never have ended otherwise. {/this was the only way it could've turned up}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.55,0:15:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.26,0:15:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth are we to tell Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.39,0:16:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We promised we’d bring him back...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.69,0:16:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She’d given up once already, \Nand we raised her hopes again.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.53,0:16:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Kath's despair will be all the harder now.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.07,0:16:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel! Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.62,0:16:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where’s Binks?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.66,0:16:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it didn’t work out after all?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.76,0:16:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.53,0:16:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least we learnt \NKelly wasn’t Binks’s real owner.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.25,0:16:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.56,0:16:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why didn’t you bring him back?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.64,0:16:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s... a good reason. {/deep }
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.88,0:16:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You should explain it to Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.14,0:16:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.21,0:16:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the situation?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.70,0:17:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I’ve heard the reason,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.75,0:17:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see why you couldn't \Ntake Binks away from Kelly.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.12,0:17:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.69,0:17:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why we had \Nto come back empty-handed.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.33,0:17:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And Miss Lewis, we’re sorry \Nwe went off without permission today.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.33,0:17:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You only wanted to help Kathleen \Nas quickly as you could.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.74,0:17:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can forgive that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.80,0:17:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I’d been in your place, \NI daresay I’d have done the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.51,0:17:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if it’s all good for Kelly, \Nwhat about Kathleen? {meaning "only kelly wins in this situation"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.48,0:17:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest, when I first heard \NKelly wasn’t the owner, I was so happy.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.79,0:17:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But... I should rather \Ntruly give up Binks this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.62,0:17:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.56,0:17:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to decide all at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.91,0:17:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right! \NYou’re his owner, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.53,0:17:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have every right to take him back.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.35,0:17:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m not really his owner either.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.90,0:17:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides, I’m already healthy, \Nwith lots of friends.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.41,0:17:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t take Binks away from Kelly.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.75,0:18:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, please, I beg you too.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.48,0:18:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let Binks stay with Kelly, \Nand let's leave it at that.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.72,0:18:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.76,0:18:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can bear it, even without Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.84,0:18:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.72,0:18:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.26,0:18:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.70,0:18:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.60,0:18:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Come and do the problem on the board.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.03,0:18:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.48,0:19:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.58,0:19:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks has come back!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.15,0:19:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.41,0:19:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.14,0:19:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.62,0:19:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.03,0:19:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.80,0:19:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? There’s something tied to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.85,0:19:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.07,0:19:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.84,0:19:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Dear twin sisters, I’m sorry I lied the other day.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.74,0:19:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to Switzerland now for the operation..."
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.21,0:19:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray, Switzerland!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.15,0:19:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"I do it because I want to become Binks’s true friend and run with him...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.33,0:19:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if the operation succeeds, \Nthe rehabilitation will be tough
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.57,0:20:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it'll be a long time until I get home.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.17,0:20:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m giving Binks back to Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.07,0:20:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In Switzerland, they’ll let me \Nhave a dog of my own.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.56,0:20:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll call him Binks the Second.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.18,0:20:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When I come back, \NI’ll bring him to meet Binks.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.58,0:20:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we’ll all run through \Nthe hills and fields together.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.15,0:20:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Run to our hearts’ content!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.18,0:20:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then—goodbye.”
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.49,0:20:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly, we’ll miss the train if we don’t go now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.13,0:20:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.00,0:20:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.78,0:20:51.62,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.50,0:20:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.51,0:21:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, gals! {sisters is cringe but idk what to call them in english}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.90,0:21:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.01,0:21:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly! Best of luck! {ganbatte}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.37,0:21:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelly! Stay strong! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.87,0:21:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation will definitely succeed! {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.79,0:21:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.71,0:21:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Switzerland has \Nthe best doctors in the field.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.99,0:21:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll be right!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.36,0:21:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on then, let’s give Kelly a cheer!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.71,0:21:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.00,0:21:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, go, Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.20,0:21:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up, keep it up, Kelly!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.77,0:22:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{fuck this}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.02,0:23:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been chosen to represent St. Clare’s...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.39,0:23:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,at the speech contest in London! {dunno what's a speech contest lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.24,0:23:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But Pat, the theme is “Our Dreams”!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.24,0:23:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Our dreams”?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.36,0:23:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.24,0:23:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen wants to be a vet. \NHilary wants to teach at a school for the blind.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:50.25,0:23:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone has dreams but us...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.57,0:23:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, how can we ever \Nwrite a speech for the contest?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.87,0:23:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.97,0:23:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.44,0:23:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Final Episode,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.44,0:24:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Thank you, St. Clare's."
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.07,0:24:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.32,0:24:04.76,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 26 \NThank you, St. Clare's {ありがとう クレア学院}
